totally lost my grip.

85
00:03:04,810 --> 00:03:06,161
Can I help you?
Oh, yes.

86
00:03:06,245 --> 00:03:09,164
Can I have a hot tea, please?

87
00:03:09,248 --> 00:03:11,449
I'd just like a large cup
of mocha powder.

88
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:12,951
David Bowie's incredibly
eccentric.

89
00:03:13,002 --> 00:03:14,753
Um, we don't take euros.

90
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:17,756
So, Honey Badger, last week,
I had a revelation.

91
00:03:17,823 --> 00:03:19,424
Now, as you may
or may not know,

92
00:03:19,491 --> 00:03:20,658
the Middle East is in chaos.

93
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:22,043
You know what started it all?

94
00:03:22,128 --> 00:03:23,828
No. A little Web site
called Wikileaks.

95
00:03:23,879 --> 00:03:25,213
You ever hear of them?

96
00:03:25,298 --> 00:03:27,515
Well, they let loose
with a couple of rumors.

97
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,117
So I told Figgins

98
00:03:29,185 --> 00:03:31,219
I wanted to resuscitate
<i>The Muckraker.</i>

99
00:03:31,304 --> 00:03:33,288
But the school newspaper was
discontinued two years ago,

100
00:03:33,356 --> 00:03:35,506
due to lack of interest.

101
00:03:35,558 --> 00:03:37,559
The newspaper is making
a comeback at this school,

102
00:03:37,643 --> 00:03:38,860
and like print
newspapers everywhere,

103
00:03:38,928 --> 00:03:40,228
we're leaner
and meaner--

104
00:03:40,313 --> 00:03:43,281
no longer concerned
with facts, fact-checking,

105
00:03:43,349 --> 00:03:44,849
integrity or facts.

106
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,985
<i>The Muckraker</i> motto?

107
00:03:47,036 --> 00:03:50,538
"If I heard it, it's probably
true or something."

108
00:03:50,623 --> 00:03:52,824
Sorry, but did you just
change disguises?

109
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:55,026
I'm pretty sure that
barista's onto me.

110
00:03:55,077 --> 00:03:56,828
Now I'm Ann Coulter.

111
00:03:56,879 --> 00:04:00,048
As you may have noticed,
I'm coming slightly unhinged.

112
00:04:00,132 --> 00:04:01,699
Ohio loves you, Ann Coulter!

113
00:04:01,751 --> 00:04:04,702
That's better.
(sighs with relief)

114
00:04:04,754 --> 00:04:07,222
Can I make an observation?

115
00:04:07,306 --> 00:04:10,258
You're always trying to destroy
Will from inside the Glee Club.

116
00:04:10,343 --> 00:04:14,212
But I would like to try getting
him <i>out</i> of the Glee Club.

117
00:04:14,263 --> 00:04:18,733
Now, I was trolling the Internet
last night and I had an idea.

118
00:04:18,818 --> 00:04:20,518
I'll drink to that.

119
00:04:24,323 --> 00:04:26,891
(school bell ringing)

120
00:04:26,942 --> 00:04:28,827
Excuse me.

121
00:04:28,894 --> 00:04:31,413
Do you know
where a gal can find

122
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,164
a pipin' hot cup of
Will Schuester?

123
00:04:33,468 --> 00:04:36,904
Oh, my God! April!

124
00:04:36,971 --> 00:04:38,606
What are you doing here?

125
00:04:38,657 --> 00:04:40,190
I thought you were on Broadway!

126
00:04:40,275 --> 00:04:44,311
I was! My all-white production of
<i>The Wiz</i> was a disaster.

127
00:04:44,362 --> 00:04:45,613
- Oh, April, I'm so sorry.
- Don't be!

128
00:04:45,664 --> 00:04:48,415
Being publicly humiliated
by the <i>New York Times</i>

129
00:04:48,483 --> 00:04:49,867
gets me to thinking--

130
00:04:49,951 --> 00:04:52,836
why am I weighing myself down
with the "Broadway classics"?

131
00:04:52,866 --> 00:04:54,175
I should just tell my own story.

132
00:04:54,205 --> 00:04:55,460
So I wrote the libretto

133
00:04:55,490 --> 00:04:58,425
to <i>Crossrhodes!</i>
<i>The April Rhodes Story.</i>

134
00:04:58,493 --> 00:04:59,627
You're writing a musical?

135
00:04:59,678 --> 00:05:01,629
Yep. That's why I'm here.

136
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:04,965
So, Will, remember how
I bought you your auditorium?

137
00:05:05,016 --> 00:05:05,966
Oh, yeah.

138
00:05:05,996 --> 00:05:09,491
Well, I'm gonna need to borrow it
cause I'm running a little low on funds.

139
00:05:09,521 --> 00:05:12,222
Extra! Extra! Read all about it!

140
00:05:12,307 --> 00:05:14,341
Get your <i>Muckraker</i> here.

141
